      <h1 class="blog-title">Month by Month: Tracking the First Year</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">Feature &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 3 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>The Month by Month section covers the first twelve months of your child's life — each month as its own entry with a photo, measurements, and a note.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>In the app</h2>

        <p>The app shows months 1 through 12 as a grid of cards. Tap any month to open it. Each month's editor has:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>A cover photo</li>
          <li>A weight and length check-in</li>
          <li>A highlight — one line for the standout milestone of that month</li>
          <li>A full note</li>
        </ul>

        <p>You don't have to fill in months in order. Add Month 3 this week, come back to the others later.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>In the web editor</h2>

        <p>The web editor at legacyodyssey.com/account/book/months gives you the same fields. Click any month in the list to open it. Some people find it easier to write longer entries from a keyboard — either works.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>On the website</h2>

        <p>On the website, filled-in months display as a scrollable row of cards. Each card shows the photo, the measurements, the highlight, and the note for that month. Months you haven't filled in don't appear.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Building it over time</h2>

        <p>Most parents fill this section as the year goes on — add the current month when it ends, let the rest wait. The website updates as you go, so family following along sees new months appear as you add them.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Part of the free tier</h2>

        <p>Month by Month is included in the free plan.</p>

